item-20000001: An order to IOP for producing Dolls. Thank goodness for our old friend, who has been giving us unfailing support.
item-30000001: Can be used in the Factory to commission the production of an IOP Doll.
item-20000002: An order to 16LAB for producing equipment. The catch of having a discount - what you receive is completely random.
item-30000002: Can be used in the Factory to commission the production of a piece of 16LAB equipment.
item-20000003: A rushed order. It does come with a risk - once the goods are delivered, they cannot be returned unless there is an issue with the quality.
item-30000003: Can be used in the Factory to instantly produce a Doll or equipment.
item-20000004: An express repair request. She is extremely eager to rejoin you on the frontlines.
item-30000004: Can be used to instantly complete the repairs on a damaged unit.
item-20000007: Proof of the OATH that you have sworn with a T-Doll who shares your feelings. It's time to take your relationship to a whole new level!
item-30000007: Can be used to establish an OATH with a T-Doll who has reached maximum Affection and raise the Affection limit.
item-20000008: It takes time for humans to learn, but if you have the money, T-Dolls can just skip the process.
item-30000008: Can be used in the Research Facility to instantly complete a T-Doll's skill training.
item-20000009: Enhancement Capsules that come in many fruity flavors. Rumor has it, to suit the taste of certain Dolls, a few new liquor-flavored versions have also been added to the selection.
item-30000009: Can be used in the Factory to enhance a T-Doll's stats, raising each non-maximized attribute by one point. All spillover points will be partially applied to other attributes.
item-20000010: A module for controlling Dummies. "One can only uninstall this with the owner's permission, making it a tool of oppression among automatons."
item-30000010: Can be used in the Factory to perform Dummy-Link on identical T-Dolls.
item-20000011: Used to exchange for a random number during the event.
item-20000012: Used to pick a specific number during the event.
item-20000013: A card for changing your name. "An opportunity for everyone (including yourself) to see you in a new light."
item-20000014: Rough Data Samples of inconsistent quality. "Will it yield the same result this time? Perhaps all it needs is a dash of inspiration."
item-30000014: Can be used in the Intelligence Center to obtain HOC Central Data or Chips through Intelligence Analysis.
item-20000015: Carefully screened samples that are more likely to yield valuable data through analysis. Slightly more likely. "At least this one looks a bit clearer."
item-30000015: Can be used in the Intelligence Center for Intelligence Analysis. Compared to Original Samples, it is easier to obtain HOC Central Data and high-rarity Chips from these.
item-20000016: If you don't pressure your analysts, you'll never know how capable your employees actually are. "In response to the other party's interests, this contract demands that you include a photo of a real kitty as bonus payment."
item-30000016: Can be used in the Intelligence Center to instantly complete a Data Analysis.
item-20000017: Data Patches that can further upgrade HOC units. Some can be obtained by dismantling fully leveled HOC units. "'When in a group of three, there is bound to be one who will have something to teach me.' That's why... 'So long, teacher.'"
item-30000017: Can be used to iterate and enhance a fully-leveled 5* HOC unit.
item-20000031: A basic skill training manual written for T-Dolls. Improvement is always a good thing! "Yay! I didn't really do anything, but well done me!"
item-30000031: Can be used in the Research Facility to provide Griffin units with Basic Skill Training.
item-20000032: An intermediate skill training manual written for T-Dolls. Don't read too deeply into it. "If I grow stronger, I will be more likely to survive, which means I can eat more ice cream. Whether I have enough money to pay for the ice cream is another matter..."
item-30000032: Can be used in the Research Facility to provide Griffin units with Intermediate Skill Training.
item-20000033: An advanced skill training manual written for T-Dolls. Very comprehensive and profound. "What's a Sweeping Monk? Why do I have to be a Sweeping Monk?" asks a Doll.
item-30000033: Can be used in the Research Facility to provide Griffin units with Advanced Skill Training.
item-20000041: White and shiny tokens that are quite rare in this day and age. "These mysterious coins were once thought to be batteries that provide Doll designers with inspiration and motivation."
item-30000041: Can be used in the Dormitories to procure Furniture and T-Doll Costumes.
item-20000042: Gift vouchers that come with making purchases. The more you buy, the more vouchers you get. IOP really is a generous company.
item-30000042: Can be used in the Dormitories to exchange for limited-time Furniture and T-Doll Costumes. Once the procurement period is over, all vouchers will be converted to tokens.
item-20000043: A high-end name card that was once exclusive to elites. Now you have one too.
item-30000043: Can be used in the Dormitories to exchange for a specific T-Doll's costume.
item-20000044: Tickets required for making Calibrations - they don't look particularly valuable. They say these are meant to prevent people from compulsively redoing Calibrations.
item-30000044: Can be used in the Research Facility to calibrate equipment or Fairies.
item-20000045: Data compiled when T-Dolls process their memories. Once screened, they can be used to upgrade a Doll's neural cloud. "You say you want me to be free, but all I want is ice cream."
item-30000045: Can be used in the Research Facility to give a T-Doll a Neural Upgrade.
item-20000046: Special combat reports for HOC units. There is an increasing number of such reports. "I hope everyone will find the real hidden treasure from these. It's important to know that you learn more from failure than success."
item-30000046: Can be used in the Garage to give HOC experience training.
item-20000050: Recycled parts from T-Dolls during pre-mission maintenance. They can be used for equipment enhancement after a little cleaning and processing. Kalina and the Commander are very pleased with this process and have given praise to the T-Doll that suggested it, but it seems that they didn't give her a raise.
item-30000050: Can be used in the Research Facility to increase equipment's Development Rate.
item-20000051: IOP has specially created this enhancement component for high-end T-Dolls with sufficient room for development. It is still in the trial stage and only available in very limited quantities.
item-30000051: Can be used to give high-rarity T-Dolls a Neural Upgrade.
item-20000100: Awarded to the Commander and the T-Dolls under their command to commend their unique and outstanding service. "Rest assured, there won't be a next time, just like the World Wars."
item-20000101: An extraordinary award for Commanders who achieve outstanding perfomance in <color=#ffb400>Theater</color>.
item-20000102: An extraordinary award for Commanders who achieve outstanding perfomance in <color=#ffb400>T-Doll Collection</color> and <color=#ffb400>Furniture Collection</color>.
item-20000103: An extraordinary award for Commanders who have shown outstanding effort in special events like the Carnival. "You've worked hard, Commander. Let's have some exercise to relax."

item-20000105: To commemorate the Commander's achievement in fighting side-by-side with Coalition Forces in an event. "Achievements in battle and exam results are two different matters. Those who need to retake their exams, don't even think about running away!"
item-20000106: To commemorate the Commander's victory in a game of Luzhanqi.
item-20000301: Data fragment of HOC BGM-71. "Sir, friendly forces spotted in targeted zones!" "Oh dear... Well, wish them luck!"
item-20000302: Data fragment of HOC AGS-30. "Actually...we all have glasses." "That's right, mine are just not as portable!"
item-20000303: Data fragment of HOC 2B14. "You remember if this is a grenade or the firework we stuffed full last night at the wine party?" "Whichever it is, I'm sure someone will wanna watch, right?"
item-20000304: Data fragment of HOC M2. "Are you sure...about this angle?" "Even if it doesn't work out, it's not my fault. It's math's."
item-20000306: Data fragments of the QLZ-04 HOC. "We've successfully reached our target destination and are beginning to replenish our ammunition... Hmm? Why can't we stuff it in?" "I told you not to go drinking with those alcoholics before we set out!"
item-20000307: Data Fragments of the HOC unit Mk 153. "Can you see the target location?" "Nope, but we just have to trust the orders we're given."

item-20004001: A type of building block toy produced from a long time ago. It is difficult to imitate due to its high production precision, so it is used as a currency in many war-torn areas and can be exchanged for many useful things.
item-20004002: Locked under the frozen grounds of ice and snow are many relic weapons of past eras. These sorts of historic wooden handguards covered in scars of war are very popular among collectors who have never stepped onto a battlefield in the safe zones.
item-20004003: Acorns from oak trees that are very rarely seen nowadays. Its price has soared recently due to becoming a collectible. You can often see uncles squatting around the safe zones, showing off their acorn bracelets.
item-20004004: A sample of Collapse fluid collected from a contaminated zone. Other than emitting a faint green light and turning people into zombies, it doesn't seem like there's much use for it. Some suspicious cultist groups are buying these up at very high prices, though.
item-20006001: Can be used to quell hunger. Also helps a tiny bit with exploration speed. It's better than nothing, I guess.
item-20006002: A basket of meat buns from a shop. It's decent enough for a simple meal. Helps a little bit with exploration speed.
item-20006003: Multiple meat buns packed in a luxurious redwood box with a dragon engraving. Plenty enough to go around. Helps a moderate bit with exploration speed.
item-20006004: A burger and fries bought separately have an extra tiny chance of winning another burger or fries, but a true aristocrat will not bother with doing this.
item-20006005: Includes everything you need to enjoy a meal alone. You get a variety of food along with a moderate chance of winning a prize. Two birds, one stone.
item-20006006: Double the calories, double the happiness, but triple the chances of winning a prize. It's always a good thing to have friends to share with.
item-20006007: A small piece of strawberry cheesecake is the best when it comes to satisfying a craving. Also increases your exploration token drops by a tiny amount.
item-20006008: Individually packaged cake delivery. These are enough to recharge your need for sweet for a week. Bring these along with you to increase exploration token drops by a small amount. Please be careful not to eat the preservatives.
item-20006009: A five pack of cakes prepared especially for sweets-addicted gourmands. It's a calorie overload if you eat it all at once, but at the same time, it'll increase your exploration token drops by a moderate amount, which would be very cost-effective.
item-20006010: Even if you're playing the role of a getaway driver in the city, you're still responsible for going downstairs to buy four cups of coffee. The city always has such an appeal, doesn't it?
item-20006011: Just like every dragon-slaying warrior needs to have a hearty meal of meat before his adventure, this box of oden is prepared for the expedition to the frozen plains. Of course, if you don't feel particularly warm after eating it, there's a likelihood that you don't need to go to the frozen plains to cool down.
item-20006012: Who would drink honey when you have a chewable honeycomb? Perhaps the bear still might, but a natural honeycomb will remind the bear about everything in a forest, and it will unconsciously wander onto the path back into the forest.
item-20006013: The fate of an ice cube is to either melt or be placed in a whiskey glass. This bowl of ice cream hopes that you will take it to the desert, give it some love, and let it melt.
item-20007001: The original purpose of the tactical bag was to allow everyone to bring more disposable equipment for their missions, but everyone just uses it to store their favorite treats.
item-20007002: The Commander asked everyone to carry some spare parts for the occasional need, but this would increase their load, so the T-Dolls devised a method to solve their problem.
item-20007003: The more things you know, the more worries you'll have. However, anxiety is a useless thing, and the only thing we can do is our best.
item-20007004: Cake, chocolate, or a love letter... What did you receive today? Or did you receive them all? You can't let the others find out if you're really receiving them!
item-20007005: Too many things on your mind will make you unable to concentrate. Therefore, it's a good strategy to distract yourself before you start thinking too much. Helian's suggestion is to take on more missions, and Kalina's suggestion is to go shopping with her as much as possible.
item-20007006: Who puts on  a spit bubble accessory when interacting with other Dolls, anyway? Some NEETs might do it to scare off people trying to pull them into their social circles.
item-20007007: Nobody knows when this disease started spreading, but if its patients could see the bubble on top of their heads, who knows if they would stop being so creepy?
item-20007008: You mean gold-diggers don't dream of gold ore? Well, gold ore falling from the sky is nothing more than a sweet dream, after all.
item-20007009: I don't know why, but as I sway to this melancholic tune, I find the past scattered in time in a purple haze...
item-20007010: So long as you enter Dreamland humming this lullaby, no matter how nightmarish your dream, you'll surely become a peerless Gold Saint.
item-20007011: Every time I catch this familiar green tune, I can't help but think that someone capable of making such holy music must love eating cherries a lot.
item-20007012: Flowers blossoming in spring, new clothes, the ground covered in soft grass... Although one can only dream of such things these days, the sense of peace they bring can carry over to reality.
item-20007013: Be tolerant. Put yourself in other people's shoes. Try to understand others... But right now I don't want to think about anything. I just want to vent my feelings without a care in the world.
item-20007014: Even if we know we're in the wrong, it can still be hurtful when we get told off. Living with negative emotions and learning to correct our mistakes are a part of growing up, but...ugh...I can't bear it anymore...
item-20007015: Humans founded the field of psychology to figure out their thoughts and feelings. Dolls are so much simpler. We just have to launch a self-learning program...Æá ÆÖóÞ¢áñп я─п╟п╨п╬п╥я▐п╠я─я▀...
item-20007016: Calculations are necessary in combat, but why are T-Dolls equipped with knowledge of advanced mathematics? Can we work as teachers once we retire?
item-20007017: Basic literary skills are important for Dolls to properly convey their thoughts... But reciting poems in the middle of a battle is a sure-fire way of getting you blacklisted. What kind of blacklist? You'll know when you're on it.
item-20007018: The sun, like the deceased, is the most beautiful in one's memory.
item-20007019: I'm sorry, the snow isn't particularly clean here. Why don't we have an electronic snowball fight on Level II instead?
item-20007020: Does the human sentiment known as "longing" carry any actual power? Dolls wouldn't know, but establishing an Oath with a person does indeed make them stronger.
item-20007021: Lurid bolete? Blue like a bruise? What do you mean, it's clearly rainbow-colored— (pukes)
item-20007022: An unlucky person is still unlucky even if they have gathered 100 clovers. Forget your fantasies and get to work.
item-20007023: Memories awakened by the falling snowflakes are always filled with sorrow – new shoes stained by sludgy snow, frostbitten ears, a hotpot knocked over by a cat.
item-20007024: Its very existence is a legend. This key to an entire era is now in your hands.
item-20007025: You now possess the sharpest spear and the strongest shield. It's as if the goddess of victory herself had kissed you on the forehead.
item-20007026: A good weapon isn't just strong, it must also have room for improvement. The same goes for people.
item-20007027: Sometimes, the outcome of a game is decided the moment you put in a game token.
item-20007028: When you have burned all your bridges and things are truly desperate, nothing is more reassuring than the sound of game tokens being shoved into the machine next to you.
item-20007029: Team assembled! Watch out, boss, this is our final form!

item-20100100: Our life is but a play in a theater; the curtain is bound to fall one day. We might as well seize every single game token and enjoy the time we have.
item-20130001: The Commander and the Dolls spend a joyful, sunny day by the sea. The cool seawater lends the Commander's skin a healthy luster, making the Commander even more charming!
item-20130002: During the day, I enjoy the time I spend together with the Dolls. But when night falls, that horrifying battle still haunts me in the dark. I know - "The past is never dead. It's not even past."
item-20130003: Several will-o'-the-wisps flicker over the forgotten graves by the road. Are they fueled by lingering resentment or unfulfilled dreams? I walk pass them unobtrusively, and they follow in equal silence. Perhaps they simply want to illuminate my path…
item-20130004:
"Commander, the hooligans are messing around in our territory again!" "Eh, just let them be."
 "But they're trying to ask the Dolls out..." "Give me a weapon. Imma beat up ten of 'em."
item-20130005: When she strikes the first match, she sees a warm fireplace. When she strikes the second match, she sees a table filled with delicious food. When she strikes the third match, she sees the Commander walking towards her, but this time, it isn't a hallucination…
item-20130006: Here is an excerpt from the Commander's diary: "...Everything felt very strange at the base today. Kalina and the Dolls were all staring at me really intensely – as if I were a walking piggy bank..."
item-20130007: Here is an excerpt from the Commander's diary: "...While I was inspecting the dorms tonight, the Dolls were all surprisingly quiet. But I kept feeling a slightly creepy breeze blowing behind me. I wonder if the ventilation system is malfunctioning..."
item-20130008: The moment you don this suit of armor, you enter a contract with it. It shall accompany you in your trials of blood and fire until you either return in triumph or meet your demise and return to ashes and dust in the currents of history.
item-20130009: Cherry blossom petals fall from the branch at the speed of five centimeters per second. Passersby in a rush brush past each other on the street at the speed of two meters per second. I can neither grasp the cherry blossom petal nor catch up to you in the crowd.
item-20130010: Marching in bad weather makes for a romantic scene in fiction, but do remember to keep warm while having fun in this artificial snow.
item-20130011: When the keeper of the night kindles the light of thoughts, the weak rejoice, the sinful tremble, and the devil bows in respect.
item-21100001: Firepower Command adds an extra 10% to both self and PzB39.
item-21100002: When in the same echelon as Grizzly, aiming time is reduced to 1 second and gain 2 stacks of charge per second.
item-21100003: When in the same echelon as FI M82, normal attacks deal an extra 10% damage to enemies directly in front of self.
item-21100004: The area in front of self is considered to be in front of AK-Alfa as well.
item-21100005: "Perseverance is the most important talent of all." When Springfield and Gr G36 are on the same echelon, Gr G36 will serve her teammates dessert. It does great things for team morale and all allies will benefit from her Damage Focus skill (effect maxed at 15%) - better watch your weight gain.
item-21100006: "I'm quite confident when it comes to making coffee blends!" When Springfield and Gr G36 are on the same echelon, Springfield will serve her teammates coffee. It does great things for team morale. With every stack, rate of fire of all allies increases by 5% (lasting for 5s, capped at 5 stacks) – better watch your weight gain.
